{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857565895,"sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","part":{"id":"prt_d795bec64001Ne96g4D1o05WNp","messageID":"msg_d795bc27e001bXyIVJIm415CAG","sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ccfaaed35372438e84001ecd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package store\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"encoding/json\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"os\"\n8: \t\"strconv\"\n9: \t\"strings\"\n10: \t\"time\"\n11: \n12: \tvalkey \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n13: \twmTypes \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n15: )\n16: \n17: type valkeyStore struct {\n18: \tcli                  valkey.Client\n19: \tsessionPrefix        string\n20: \texpiryIndexKey       string\n21: \tlastActivityIndexKey string\n22: }\n23: \n24: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n25: \taddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n26: \tif addr == \"\" {\n27: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n28: \t}\n29: \n30: \taddresses := strings.Split(addr, \",\")\n31: \n32: \tpassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n33: \tpasswordRequired := true\n34: \tif val := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); val != \"\" {\n35: \t\tpasswordRequired = strings.ToLower(val) != \"false\"\n36: \t}\n37: \n38: \tif passwordRequired && password == \"\" {\n39: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n40: \t}\n41: \n42: \tdisableCache := false\n43: \tif val := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); val != \"\" {\n44: \t\tdisableCache, _ = strconv.ParseBool(val)\n45: \t}\n46: \n47: \tforceSingle := false\n48: \tif val := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); val != \"\" {\n49: \t\tforceSingle, _ = strconv.ParseBool(val)\n50: \t}\n51: \n52: \topt := valkey.ClientOption{\n53: \t\tInitAddress:  addresses,\n54: \t\tPassword:     password,\n55: \t\tDisableCache: disableCache,\n56: \t}\n57: \n58: \tif forceSingle {\n59: \t\topt.ForceSingleClient = true\n60: \t}\n61: \n62: \treturn &opt, nil\n63: }\n64: \n65: func NewValkeyStore(opts *valkey.ClientOption) (*valkeyStore, error) {\n66: \tclient, err := valkey.NewClient(*opts)\n67: \tif err != nil {\n68: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)\n69: \t}\n70: \n71: \treturn &valkeyStore{\n72: \t\tcli:                  client,\n73: \t\tsessionPrefix:        sessionPrefix,\n74: \t\texpiryIndexKey:       expiryIndexKey,\n75: \t\tlastActivityIndexKey: lastActivityIndexKey,\n76: \t}, nil\n77: }\n78: \n79: func (vs *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n80: \tresp := vs.cli.B().Ping().Build()\n81: \tresult, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, resp).ToString()\n82: \tif err != nil {\n83: \t\treturn err\n84: \t}\n85: \tif result != \"PONG\" {\n86: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %q\", result)\n87: \t}\n88: \treturn nil\n89: }\n90: \n91: func (vs *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n92: \tkey := vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n93: \tcmd := vs.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()\n94: \tresult, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, cmd).ToString()\n95: \tif err != nil {\n96: \t\tif valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n97: \t\t\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\n98: \t\t}\n99: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get sandbox: %w\", err)\n100: \t}\n101: \n102: \tvar info wmTypes.SandboxInfo\n103: \tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(result), &info); err != nil {\n104: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n105: \t}\n106: \treturn &info, nil\n107: }\n108: \n109: func (vs *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *wmTypes.SandboxInfo) error {\n110: \tif sandboxStore == nil {\n111: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n112: \t}\n113: \tif sandboxStore.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n114: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox ExpiresAt cannot be zero\")\n115: \t}\n116: \n117: \tkey := vs.sessionPrefix + sandboxStore.SessionID\n118: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandboxStore)\n119: \tif err != nil {\n120: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n121: \t}\n122: \n123: \tnow := time.Now().Unix()\n124: \texpiresAt := sandboxStore.ExpiresAt.Unix()\n125: \tlastActivity := sandboxStore.LastActivityAt.Unix()\n126: \tif lastActivity == 0 {\n127: \t\tlastActivity = now\n128: \t}\n129: \n130: \tsetCmd := vs.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build()\n131: \texpiryCmd := vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(expiresAt), sandboxStore.SessionID).Build()\n132: \tlastActivityCmd := vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(lastActivity), sandboxStore.SessionID).Build()\n133: \n134: \tresponses := vs.cli.DoMulti(ctx, setCmd, expiryCmd, lastActivityCmd)\n135: \n136: \tsetResult, err := responses[0].AsBool()\n137: \tif err != nil {\n138: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"SETNX failed: %w\", err)\n139: \t}\n140: \tif !setResult {\n141: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"session %s already exists\", sandboxStore.SessionID)\n142: \t}\n143: \n144: \tif err := responses[1].Error(); err != nil {\n145: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"ZADD expiry failed: %w\", err)\n146: \t}\n147: \tif err := responses[2].Error(); err != nil {\n148: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"ZADD last_activity failed: %w\", err)\n149: \t}\n150: \n151: \treturn nil\n152: }\n153: \n154: func (vs *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *wmTypes.SandboxInfo) error {\n155: \tif sandboxStore == nil {\n156: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n157: \t}\n158: \n159: \tkey := vs.sessionPrefix + sandboxStore.SessionID\n160: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandboxStore)\n161: \tif err != nil {\n162: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n163: \t}\n164: \n165: \tcmd := vs.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()\n166: \tresult, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, cmd).ToString()\n167: \tif err != nil {\n168: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"SET XX failed: %w\", err)\n169: \t}\n170: \tif result != \"OK\" {\n171: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n172: \t}\n173: \n174: \treturn nil\n175: }\n176: \n177: func (vs *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n178: \tkey := vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n179: \n180: \tdelCmd := vs.cli.B().Del().Key(key).Build()\n181: \texpiryCmd := vs.cli.B().Zrem().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()\n182: \tlastActivityCmd := vs.cli.B().Zrem().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()\n183: \n184: \tresponses := vs.cli.DoMulti(ctx, delCmd, expiryCmd, lastActivityCmd)\n185: \n186: \tfor i, resp := range responses {\n187: \t\tif err := resp.Error(); err != nil {\n188: \t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"command %d failed: %w\", i, err)\n189: \t\t}\n190: \t}\n191: \n192: \treturn nil\n193: }\n194: \n195: func (vs *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n196: \tif limit <= 0 {\n197: \t\treturn nil, nil\n198: \t}\n199: \n200: \tcmd := vs.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(vs.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()\n201: \tsessionIDs, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, cmd).AsStrSlice()\n202: \tif err != nil {\n203: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to query expired sessions: %w\", err)\n204: \t}\n205: \n206: \treturn vs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n207: }\n208: \n209: func (vs *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n210: \tif limit <= 0 {\n211: \t\treturn nil, nil\n212: \t}\n213: \n214: \tcmd := vs.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()\n215: \tsessionIDs, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, cmd).AsStrSlice()\n216: \tif err != nil {\n217: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to query inactive sessions: %w\", err)\n218: \t}\n219: \n220: \treturn vs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n221: }\n222: \n223: func (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n224: \tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n225: \t\treturn nil, nil\n226: \t}\n227: \n228: \tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n229: \tfor i, sid := range sessionIDs {\n230: \t\tkeys[i] = vs.sessionPrefix + sid\n231: \t}\n232: \n233: \tmgetCmd := vs.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()\n234: \tresults, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, mgetCmd).AsStrSlice()\n235: \tif err != nil {\n236: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"MGET failed: %w\", err)\n237: \t}\n238: \n239: \tvar result []*wmTypes.SandboxInfo\n240: \tfor i, data := range results {\n241: \t\tif data == \"\" {\n242: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"orphaned ZSET member: session %s not found\", sessionIDs[i])\n243: \t\t\tcontinue\n244: \t\t}\n245: \n246: \t\tvar info wmTypes.SandboxInfo\n247: \t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &info); err != nil {\n248: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"failed to unmarshal session %s: %v\", sessionIDs[i], err)\n249: \t\t\tcontinue\n250: \t\t}\n251: \t\tresult = append(result, &info)\n252: \t}\n253: \n254: \treturn result, nil\n255: }\n256: \n257: func (vs *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n258: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n259: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID cannot be empty\")\n260: \t}\n261: \n262: \tkey := vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n263: \n264: \texistsCmd := vs.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build()\n265: \tcount, err := vs.cli.Do(ctx, existsCmd).AsInt64()\n266: \tif err != nil {\n267: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"EXISTS failed: %w\", err)\n268: \t}\n269: \tif count == 0 {\n270: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n271: \t}\n272: \n273: \tif at.IsZero() {\n274: \t\tat = time.Now()\n275: \t}\n276: \n277: \tzaddCmd := vs.cli.B().Zadd().Key(vs.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build()\n278: \treturn vs.cli.Do(ctx, zaddCmd).Error()\n279: }\n280: \n281: func (vs *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n282: \tvs.cli.Close()\n283: \treturn nil\n284: }\n\n(End of file - total 284 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tvalkey \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n\twmTypes \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n\tcli                  valkey.Client\n\tsessionPrefix        string\n\texpiryIndexKey       string","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go","time":{"start":1775857565852,"end":1775857565894}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857565897,"sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","part":{"id":"prt_d795bfbf1001gEDtDXobX2TqLl","messageID":"msg_d795bc27e001bXyIVJIm415CAG","sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_37914882c168498fa97fc6a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package store\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"encoding/json\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"os\"\n8: \t\"strings\"\n9: \t\"time\"\n10: \n11: \t\"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n12: \twmTypes \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n13: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n14: )\n15: \n16: type redisStore struct {\n17: \tcli                  *redis.Client\n18: \tsessionPrefix        string\n19: \texpiryIndexKey       string\n20: \tlastActivityIndexKey string\n21: }\n22: \n23: func makeRedisOptions() (*redis.Options, error) {\n24: \taddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n25: \tif addr == \"\" {\n26: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n27: \t}\n28: \n29: \tpassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n30: \tpasswordRequired := true\n31: \tif val := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); val != \"\" {\n32: \t\tpasswordRequired = strings.ToLower(val) != \"false\"\n33: \t}\n34: \n35: \tif passwordRequired && password == \"\" {\n36: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n37: \t}\n38: \n39: \treturn &redis.Options{\n40: \t\tAddr:     addr,\n41: \t\tPassword: password,\n42: \t}, nil\n43: }\n44: \n45: func NewRedisStore(opts *redis.Options) *redisStore {\n46: \tclient := redis.NewClient(opts)\n47: \treturn &redisStore{\n48: \t\tcli:                  client,\n49: \t\tsessionPrefix:        sessionPrefix,\n50: \t\texpiryIndexKey:       expiryIndexKey,\n51: \t\tlastActivityIndexKey: lastActivityIndexKey,\n52: \t}\n53: }\n54: \n55: func (rs *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n56: \tresp, err := rs.cli.Ping(ctx).Result()\n57: \tif err != nil {\n58: \t\treturn err\n59: \t}\n60: \tif resp != \"PONG\" {\n61: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %q\", resp)\n62: \t}\n63: \treturn nil\n64: }\n65: \n66: func (rs *redisStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n67: \tkey := rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n68: \tdata, err := rs.cli.Get(ctx, key).Result()\n69: \tif err != nil {\n70: \t\tif err == redis.Nil {\n71: \t\t\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\n72: \t\t}\n73: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get sandbox: %w\", err)\n74: \t}\n75: \n76: \tvar info wmTypes.SandboxInfo\n77: \tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &info); err != nil {\n78: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n79: \t}\n80: \treturn &info, nil\n81: }\n82: \n83: func (rs *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *wmTypes.SandboxInfo) error {\n84: \tif sandboxStore == nil {\n85: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n86: \t}\n87: \tif sandboxStore.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n88: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox ExpiresAt cannot be zero\")\n89: \t}\n90: \n91: \tkey := rs.sessionPrefix + sandboxStore.SessionID\n92: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandboxStore)\n93: \tif err != nil {\n94: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n95: \t}\n96: \n97: \tnow := time.Now().Unix()\n98: \texpiresAt := sandboxStore.ExpiresAt.Unix()\n99: \tlastActivity := sandboxStore.LastActivityAt.Unix()\n100: \tif lastActivity == 0 {\n101: \t\tlastActivity = now\n102: \t}\n103: \n104: \tpipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n105: \n106: \tsetCmd := pipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\n107: \n108: \texpiryCmd := pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, redis.Z{\n109: \t\tScore:  float64(expiresAt),\n110: \t\tMember: sandboxStore.SessionID,\n111: \t})\n112: \n113: \tlastActivityCmd := pipe.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redis.Z{\n114: \t\tScore:  float64(lastActivity),\n115: \t\tMember: sandboxStore.SessionID,\n116: \t})\n117: \n118: \t_, err = pipe.Exec(ctx)\n119: \tif err != nil {\n120: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"pipeline failed: %w\", err)\n121: \t}\n122: \n123: \tif !setCmd.Val() {\n124: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"session %s already exists\", sandboxStore.SessionID)\n125: \t}\n126: \n127: \tif err := setCmd.Err(); err != nil {\n128: \t\treturn err\n129: \t}\n130: \tif err := expiryCmd.Err(); err != nil {\n131: \t\treturn err\n132: \t}\n133: \tif err := lastActivityCmd.Err(); err != nil {\n134: \t\treturn err\n135: \t}\n136: \n137: \treturn nil\n138: }\n139: \n140: func (rs *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *wmTypes.SandboxInfo) error {\n141: \tif sandboxStore == nil {\n142: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n143: \t}\n144: \n145: \tkey := rs.sessionPrefix + sandboxStore.SessionID\n146: \n147: \texistsCmd := rs.cli.Exists(ctx, key)\n148: \tcount, err := existsCmd.Result()\n149: \tif err != nil {\n150: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to check existence: %w\", err)\n151: \t}\n152: \tif count == 0 {\n153: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n154: \t}\n155: \n156: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandboxStore)\n157: \tif err != nil {\n158: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n159: \t}\n160: \n161: \tsetCmd := rs.cli.Set(ctx, key, data, redis.KeepTTL)\n162: \tif setCmd.Err() != nil {\n163: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update sandbox: %w\", setCmd.Err())\n164: \t}\n165: \n166: \treturn nil\n167: }\n168: \n169: func (rs *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n170: \tkey := rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n171: \n172: \tpipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n173: \tpipe.Del(ctx, key)\n174: \tpipe.ZRem(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, sessionID)\n175: \tpipe.ZRem(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, sessionID)\n176: \n177: \t_, err := pipe.Exec(ctx)\n178: \treturn err\n179: }\n180: \n181: func (rs *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n182: \tif limit <= 0 {\n183: \t\treturn nil, nil\n184: \t}\n185: \n186: \tzCmd := rs.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, rs.expiryIndexKey, &redis.ZRangeBy{\n187: \t\tMin:    \"-inf\",\n188: \t\tMax:    fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()),\n189: \t\tOffset: 0,\n190: \t\tCount:  limit,\n191: \t})\n192: \n193: \tsessionIDs, err := zCmd.Result()\n194: \tif err != nil {\n195: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to query expired sessions: %w\", err)\n196: \t}\n197: \n198: \treturn rs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n199: }\n200: \n201: func (rs *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n202: \tif limit <= 0 {\n203: \t\treturn nil, nil\n204: \t}\n205: \n206: \tzCmd := rs.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, &redis.ZRangeBy{\n207: \t\tMin:    \"-inf\",\n208: \t\tMax:    fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()),\n209: \t\tOffset: 0,\n210: \t\tCount:  limit,\n211: \t})\n212: \n213: \tsessionIDs, err := zCmd.Result()\n214: \tif err != nil {\n215: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to query inactive sessions: %w\", err)\n216: \t}\n217: \n218: \treturn rs.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n219: }\n220: \n221: func (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*wmTypes.SandboxInfo, error) {\n222: \tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n223: \t\treturn nil, nil\n224: \t}\n225: \n226: \tpipe := rs.cli.Pipeline()\n227: \tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n228: \tfor i, sid := range sessionIDs {\n229: \t\tkeys[i] = rs.sessionPrefix + sid\n230: \t\tpipe.Get(ctx, keys[i])\n231: \t}\n232: \n233: \tcmds, err := pipe.Exec(ctx)\n234: \tif err != nil && err != redis.Nil {\n235: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"pipeline failed: %w\", err)\n236: \t}\n237: \n238: \tvar result []*wmTypes.SandboxInfo\n239: \tfor i, cmd := range cmds {\n240: \t\tdata, err := cmd.(*redis.StringCmd).Result()\n241: \t\tif err == redis.Nil {\n242: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"orphaned ZSET member: session %s not found\", sessionIDs[i])\n243: \t\t\tcontinue\n244: \t\t}\n245: \t\tif err != nil {\n246: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"failed to get session %s: %v\", sessionIDs[i], err)\n247: \t\t\tcontinue\n248: \t\t}\n249: \n250: \t\tvar info wmTypes.SandboxInfo\n251: \t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &info); err != nil {\n252: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"failed to unmarshal session %s: %v\", sessionIDs[i], err)\n253: \t\t\tcontinue\n254: \t\t}\n255: \t\tresult = append(result, &info)\n256: \t}\n257: \n258: \treturn result, nil\n259: }\n260: \n261: func (rs *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n262: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n263: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID cannot be empty\")\n264: \t}\n265: \n266: \tkey := rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n267: \n268: \tgetCmd := rs.cli.Get(ctx, key)\n269: \tif getCmd.Err() == redis.Nil {\n270: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n271: \t}\n272: \tif getCmd.Err() != nil {\n273: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to check session: %w\", getCmd.Err())\n274: \t}\n275: \n276: \tif at.IsZero() {\n277: \t\tat = time.Now()\n278: \t}\n279: \n280: \tzCmd := rs.cli.ZAdd(ctx, rs.lastActivityIndexKey, redis.Z{\n281: \t\tScore:  float64(at.Unix()),\n282: \t\tMember: sessionID,\n283: \t})\n284: \n285: \treturn zCmd.Err()\n286: }\n287: \n288: func (rs *redisStore) Close() error {\n289: \treturn rs.cli.Close()\n290: }\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n\twmTypes \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\ntype redisStore struct {\n\tcli                  *redis.Client\n\tsessionPrefix        string\n\texpiryIndexKey       string\n\tlastActivityIndexKey string","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go","time":{"start":1775857565858,"end":1775857565896}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857565900,"sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","part":{"id":"prt_d795bf686001mdyNvpo7puuRAK","messageID":"msg_d795bc27e001bXyIVJIm415CAG","sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d344717411c54f129a4adb5e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-014 — Valkey Store Implementation\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Type:** New Feature\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: \n12: This specification defines the Valkey implementation of the `Store` interface for session persistence in the AgentCube sandbox orchestration system. The Valkey store provides an alternative backend to Redis with compatible operations using the `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client library.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Requirements\n17: \n18: ### R-1: Valkey Store Structure\n19: \n20: **Given** the Valkey store implementation  \n21: **When** the store is instantiated  \n22: **Then** it SHALL have the following structure:\n23: \n24: ```go\n25: type valkeyStore struct {\n26:     cli                  valkey.Client\n27:     sessionPrefix        string\n28:     expiryIndexKey       string\n29:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n30: }\n31: ```\n32: \n33: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n34: \n35: ```gherkin\n36: Scenario: Valkey store has correct fields\n37:   Given the valkeyStore struct is defined\n38:   When the struct is inspected\n39:   Then it SHALL have cli field of type valkey.Client\n40:   And it SHALL have sessionPrefix string field\n41:   And it SHALL have expiryIndexKey string field\n42:   And it SHALL have lastActivityIndexKey string field\n43: \n44: Scenario: Valkey store uses same key patterns as Redis\n45:   Given valkeyStore constants are defined\n46:   When the values are checked\n47:   Then sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n48:   And expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n49:   And lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### R-2: Valkey Client Connection Options\n55: \n56: **Given** Valkey store initialization  \n57: **When** connection options are built  \n58: **Then** the system SHALL construct `valkey.ClientOption` with:\n59: \n60: - `InitAddress`: Split from `VALKEY_ADDR` by commas\n61: - `Password`: From `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n62: - `DisableCache`: From `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, true enables)\n63: - `ForceSingleClient`: From `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, true enables)\n64: \n65: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n66: \n67: ```gherkin\n68: Scenario: Single address InitAddress\n69:   Given VALKEY_ADDR=\"valkey:6379\"\n70:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n71:   Then InitAddress SHALL be []string{\"valkey:6379\"}\n72: \n73: Scenario: Multiple addresses InitAddress\n74:   Given VALKEY_ADDR=\"node1:6379,node2:6379,node3:6379\"\n75:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n76:   Then InitAddress SHALL be []string{\"node1:6379\", \"node2:6379\", \"node3:6379\"}\n77: \n78: Scenario: Password provided\n79:   Given VALKEY_PASSWORD=\"secret123\"\n80:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n81:   Then Password SHALL be \"secret123\"\n82: \n83: Scenario: DisableCache enabled\n84:   Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"\n85:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n86:   Then DisableCache SHALL be true\n87: \n88: Scenario: DisableCache disabled\n89:   Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"false\"\n90:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n91:   Then DisableCache SHALL be false\n92: \n93: Scenario: DisableCache invalid value\n94:   Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"invalid\"\n95:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n96:   Then DisableCache SHALL be false (ParseBool fallback)\n97: \n98: Scenario: ForceSingleClient enabled\n99:   Given VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\n100:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n101:   Then ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n102: \n103: Scenario: ForceSingleClient disabled\n104:   Given VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE unset\n105:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n106:   Then ForceSingleClient SHALL be false\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ### R-3: Valkey Environment Variables\n112: \n113: **Given** Valkey store initialization  \n114: **When** environment variables are read  \n115: **Then** the system SHALL require/process:\n116: \n117: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n118: |----------|----------|-------|\n119: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list |\n120: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n121: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | Default `true`, case-insensitive |\n122: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | Default `false`, ParseBool |\n123: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | Default `false`, ParseBool |\n124: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n125: \n126: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n127: \n128: ```gherkin\n129: Scenario: VALKEY_ADDR required\n130:   Given VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n131:   When Valkey store initializes\n132:   Then initialization SHALL fail with error indicating missing VALKEY_ADDR\n133: \n134: Scenario: VALKEY_PASSWORD required by default\n135:   Given VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty\n136:   And VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED is unset\n137:   When Valkey store initializes\n138:   Then initialization SHALL fail with error stating password required\n139: \n140: Scenario: VALKEY_PASSWORD disabled\n141:   Given VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty\n142:   And VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\n143:   When Valkey store initializes\n144:   Then connection SHALL proceed with empty password\n145: \n146: Scenario: STORE_TYPE must be valkey\n147:   Given STORE_TYPE=\"redis\"\n148:   When Valkey store initialization is attempted\n149:   Then the Redis implementation SHALL be selected instead\n150: \n151: Scenario: STORE_TYPE case insensitive\n152:   Given STORE_TYPE=\"VALKEY\"\n153:   When Storage() initializes\n154:   Then Valkey implementation SHALL be constructed\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ### R-4: Ping Operation\n160: \n161: **Given** a Valkey store instance  \n162: **When** `Ping(ctx)` is called  \n163: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n164: \n165: - Execute `B().Ping()` command\n166: - Expect string response `PONG`\n167: - Return error if response is not `PONG`\n168: \n169: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n170: \n171: ```gherkin\n172: Scenario: Ping succeeds\n173:   Given a healthy Valkey server\n174:   When Ping(ctx) is called\n175:   Then B().Ping() SHALL be executed\n176:   And the response SHALL be \"PONG\"\n177:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n178: \n179: Scenario: Ping fails\n180:   Given Valkey server is unreachable\n181:   When Ping(ctx) is called\n182:   Then B().Ping() SHALL return error\n183:   And non-nil error SHALL be returned\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ### R-5: GetSandboxBySessionID Operation\n189: \n190: **Given** a session ID  \n191: **When** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called  \n192: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n193: \n194: - Construct key as `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n195: - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n196: - Return `ErrNotFound` if `IsValkeyNil` is true\n197: - Decode JSON bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo` on success\n198: \n199: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n200: \n201: ```gherkin\n202: Scenario: Get existing session\n203:   Given session \"abc-123\" exists with valid JSON data\n204:   When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n205:   Then B().Get().Key(\"session:abc-123\") SHALL be executed\n206:   And JSON SHALL be decoded to *types.SandboxInfo\n207:   And the SandboxInfo SHALL be returned with nil error\n208: \n209: Scenario: Get missing session\n210:   Given no key \"session:abc-123\" exists\n211:   When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n212:   Then IsValkeyNil SHALL return true\n213:   And ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n214: \n215: Scenario: Get with invalid JSON\n216:   Given key \"session:abc-123\" contains invalid JSON\n217:   When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n218:   Then JSON decoding SHALL fail\n219:   And appropriate error SHALL be returned\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ### R-6: StoreSandbox Operation\n225: \n226: **Given** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo`  \n227: **When** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n228: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n229: \n230: - Reject nil sandbox with error\n231: - Reject zero `ExpiresAt` with error\n232: - Execute `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity in `DoMulti`\n233: - Use `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` for expiry score\n234: - Use `float64(time.Now().Unix())` for last-activity score\n235: \n236: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n237: \n238: ```gherkin\n239: Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n240:   Given StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\n241:   When the method executes\n242:   Then error SHALL indicate sandbox is nil\n243:   And no backend operation SHALL occur\n244: \n245: Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n246:   Given sandbox with ExpiresAt = time.Time{}\n247:   When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n248:   Then error SHALL indicate ExpiresAt is invalid\n249:   And no backend operation SHALL occur\n250: \n251: Scenario: StoreSandbox succeeds\n252:   Given valid sandbox with SessionID=\"abc\", ExpiresAt=Unix(1000)\n253:   When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n254:   Then DoMulti SHALL execute:\n255:     | Command | Key | Member | Score |\n256:     | SETNX | session:abc | - | - |\n257:     | ZADD | session:expiry | abc | 1000 |\n258:     | ZADD | session:last_activity | abc | <now.Unix()> |\n259:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n260: \n261: Scenario: Duplicate store fails\n262:   Given session \"abc\" already exists\n263:   When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) with same SessionID is called\n264:   Then SETNX SHALL return 0\n265:   And error SHALL be returned\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### R-7: UpdateSandbox Operation\n271: \n272: **Given** an existing session  \n273: **When** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n274: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n275: \n276: - Execute `SET` with `XX` option (key must exist)\n277: - Require response `\"OK\"` for success\n278: - NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries\n279: \n280: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n281: \n282: ```gherkin\n283: Scenario: Update existing session\n284:   Given session \"abc\" exists with JSON value V1\n285:   When UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) with updated data is called\n286:   Then SET session:abc value XX SHALL be executed\n287:   And response SHALL be \"OK\"\n288:   And JSON value SHALL be updated to V2\n289:   And session:expiry and session:last_activity SHALL be unchanged\n290: \n291: Scenario: Update missing session\n292:   Given session key \"session:abc\" does not exist\n293:   When UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n294:   Then SET XX SHALL not update (key missing)\n295:   And response SHALL not be \"OK\"\n296:   And error SHALL be returned indicating key not exists\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ### R-8: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Operation\n302: \n303: **Given** a session ID  \n304: **When** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called  \n305: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n306: \n307: - Execute `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity in `DoMulti`\n308: - Remove session from all three storage locations\n309: \n310: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n311: \n312: ```gherkin\n313: Scenario: Full removal\n314:   Given session \"abc\" exists in main key and both ZSETs\n315:   When DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n316:   Then DoMulti SHALL execute:\n317:     | Command | Key | Member |\n318:     | DEL | session:abc | - |\n319:     | ZREM | session:expiry | abc |\n320:     | ZREM | session:last_activity | abc |\n321:   And all three operations SHALL succeed\n322:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n323: \n324: Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n325:   Given session \"abc\" does not exist\n326:   When DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n327:   Then DEL and ZREM operations SHALL complete without error\n328:   And nil error SHALL be returned (idempotent)\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ### R-9: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n334: \n335: **Given** a time `before` and limit  \n336: **When** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called  \n337: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n338: \n339: - Return `nil, nil` if `limit <= 0`\n340: - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix())`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n341: - Use `MGET` to load JSON for each session ID\n342: - Skip orphaned ZSET members (missing JSON keys)\n343: \n344: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n345: \n346: ```gherkin\n347: Scenario: List expired sessions\n348:   Given session:expiry contains members with scores [500, 800, 1200]\n349:   And before = Unix(1000) and limit = 10\n350:   When ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n351:   Then Zrangebyscore SHALL select members with scores <= 999\n352:   And members with scores 500 and 800 SHALL be returned\n353:   And MGET SHALL load JSON for each member\n354:   And slice of SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n355: \n356: Scenario: Zero limit\n357:   Given limit = 0\n358:   When ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0) is called\n359:   Then nil, nil SHALL be returned immediately\n360: \n361: Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n362:   Given session:expiry contains \"orphan\" but no session:orphan key\n363:   When ListExpiredSandboxes loads sessions\n364:   Then \"orphan\" SHALL be omitted from results\n365:   And no error SHALL be returned for the orphan\n366: ```\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ### R-10: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n371: \n372: **Given** a time `before` and limit  \n373: **When** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called  \n374: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n375: \n376: - Return `nil, nil` if `limit <= 0`\n377: - Execute `Zrangebyscore` on `session:last_activity` with same parameters as expired\n378: - Use `MGET` to load JSON for each session ID\n379: - Skip orphaned ZSET members\n380: \n381: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n382: \n383: ```gherkin\n384: Scenario: List inactive sessions\n385:   Given session:last_activity contains members with scores [500, 800, 1200]\n386:   And before = Unix(1000) and limit = 10\n387:   When ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n388:   Then Zrangebyscore SHALL select members with scores <= 999\n389:   And members with scores 500 and 800 SHALL be returned\n390:   And slice of SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n391: \n392: Scenario: Zero limit\n393:   Given limit = 0\n394:   When ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 0) is called\n395:   Then nil, nil SHALL be returned immediately\n396: ```\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ### R-11: UpdateSessionLastActivity Operation\n401: \n402: **Given** a session ID and timestamp  \n403: **When** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` is called  \n404: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n405: \n406: - Reject empty session ID with error\n407: - Use `time.Now()` if `at` is zero time\n408: - Verify session key exists using `Exists` (must return 1)\n409: - Execute `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with `float64(at.Unix())`\n410: - Return `ErrNotFound` if session key does not exist\n411: \n412: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n413: \n414: ```gherkin\n415: Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n416:   Given UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", time.Now()) is called\n417:   When the method executes\n418:   Then error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n419:   And no backend operation SHALL occur\n420: \n421: Scenario: Update last activity\n422:   Given session \"abc\" exists\n423:   And at = Unix(2000)\n424:   When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at) is called\n425:   Then Exists(\"session:abc\") SHALL return 1\n426:   And ZADD session:last_activity abc 2000 SHALL be executed\n427:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n428: \n429: Scenario: Zero time uses Now\n430:   Given session \"abc\" exists\n431:   And at = time.Time{} (zero value)\n432:   When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at) is called\n433:   Then ZADD SHALL use time.Now().Unix() as score\n434: \n435: Scenario: Update missing session\n436:   Given session \"abc\" does not exist\n437:   When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Now()) is called\n438:   Then Exists SHALL return 0\n439:   And ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n440:   And no ZADD SHALL occur\n441: ```\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ### R-12: Close Operation\n446: \n447: **Given** a Valkey store instance  \n448: **When** `Close()` is called  \n449: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n450: \n451: - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n452: - Return `nil`\n453: \n454: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n455: \n456: ```gherkin\n457: Scenario: Close connection\n458:   Given valkeyStore with active client connection\n459:   When Close() is called\n460:   Then vs.cli.Close() SHALL be executed\n461:   And nil SHALL be returned\n462: ```\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ### R-13: ZSET Score Semantics\n467: \n468: **Given** ZSET operations for indices  \n469: **When** scores are assigned  \n470: **Then** the system SHALL use:\n471: \n472: - **Expiry index:** `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\n473: - **Last activity index:** `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`, `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n474: \n475: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n476: \n477: ```gherkin\n478: Scenario: Expiry score from ExpiresAt\n479:   Given sandbox.ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)\n480:   When StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n481:   Then score SHALL be 1234567890.0\n482: \n483: Scenario: Last activity score from current time\n484:   Given StoreSandbox is called at time.Unix(1000, 0)\n485:   When last-activity index is updated\n486:   Then score SHALL be 1000.0\n487: \n488: Scenario: Last activity score from provided time\n489:   Given UpdateSessionLastActivity with at = time.Unix(2000, 0)\n490:   When last-activity index is updated\n491:   Then score SHALL be 2000.0\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ### R-14: MGET Optimization Note\n497: \n498: **Given** loading multiple sessions by IDs  \n499: **When** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` is called  \n500: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n501: \n502: - Build all `session:{id}` keys\n503: - Use single `MGET` command for batch retrieval\n504: - Note: Keys should be in same cluster slot for deployment consideration\n505: \n506: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n507: \n508: ```gherkin\n509: Scenario: Batch load with MGET\n510:   Given session IDs [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"] all exist\n511:   When loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n512:   Then single MGET session:a session:b session:c SHALL be executed\n513:   And all three SHALL be loaded efficiently\n514: \n515: Scenario: Partial MGET results\n516:   Given session IDs [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"] where only \"a\" and \"c\" exist\n517:   When loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n518:   Then MGET SHALL return values for \"a\", \"\", \"c\"\n519:   And only \"a\" and \"c\" SHALL be in returned slice\n520: ```\n521: \n522: ---\n523: \n524: ## Dependencies\n525: \n526: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n527: |------------|--------|-------|\n528: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n529: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Logging in makeValkeyOptions |\n530: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo type |\n531: \n532: ---\n533: \n534: ## Data Structures\n535: \n536: ### valkeyStore\n537: \n538: ```go\n539: type valkeyStore struct {\n540:     cli                  valkey.Client\n541:     sessionPrefix        string\n542:     expiryIndexKey       string\n543:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n544: }\n545: ```\n546: \n547: ### Environment Configuration\n548: \n549: ```go\n550: type ValkeyConfig struct {\n551:     Addr                 string   // VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated)\n552:     Password             string   // VALKEY_PASSWORD\n553:     PasswordRequired     bool     // VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED (default true)\n554:     DisableCache         bool     // VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE (default false)\n555:     ForceSingleClient    bool     // VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE (default false)\n556: }\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ## Files to Create/Modify\n562: \n563: | File | Action | Description |\n564: |------|--------|-------------|\n565: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Create | Valkey implementation of Store interface |\n566: | `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for Valkey operations |\n567: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Modify | Add valkeyStoreType constant and Valkey initialization |\n568: \n569: ---\n570: \n571: ## Testing Strategy\n572: \n573: 1. **Unit Tests**:\n574:    - Mock Valkey client with gock/valkey mock\n575:    - Test all failure modes (connection errors, nil responses)\n576:    - Test environment variable parsing\n577: \n578: 2. **Integration Tests**:\n579:    - TestContainer with Valkey instance\n580:    - Verify all Store interface operations\n581:    - Test ZSET score semantics\n582: \n583: 3. **Compatibility Tests**:\n584:    - Verify same behavior as Redis implementation\n585:    - Test identical GIVEN/WHEN/THEN outcomes\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## Security Considerations\n590: \n591: - **Password Storage**: Loaded from environment variable (never committed)\n592: - **Connection**: TLS recommended for production Valkey connections\n593: - **Logging**: Password values MUST NOT be logged (use klog carefully)\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## Open Questions\n598: \n599: 1. Should cluster mode be explicitly supported with slot hashing?\n600: 2. Should connection pooling parameters be configurable?\n601: 3. Should Valkey-specific features (e.g., JSON module) be leveraged?\n\n(End of file - total 601 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-014 — Valkey Store Implementation\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** New Feature\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis specification defines the Valkey implementation of the `Store` interface for session persistence in the AgentCube sandbox orchestration system. The Valkey store provides an alternative backend to Redis with compatible operations using the `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### R-1: Valkey Store Structure\n\n**Given** the Valkey store implementation  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857565857,"end":1775857565897}}}}
