{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857589792,"sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","part":{"id":"prt_d795c5388001V5QfHtEYbLoEm0","messageID":"msg_d795c010a001kGEFU0ud2R2ONR","sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1609f416200546c0a9b141e3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/doc.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/doc.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // Package store provides persistent storage for sandbox session metadata in the agentcube project.\n2: //\n3: // # Overview\n4: //\n5: // The session storage system enables:\n6: //   - Session persistence: Store and retrieve sandbox information keyed by session ID\n7: //   - Garbage collection support: Index sessions by expiry time and last activity for cleanup operations\n8: //   - Backend flexibility: Support both Redis and Valkey storage providers via configuration-based selection\n9: //   - Singleton access: Thread-safe initialization and global access pattern\n10: //\n11: // # Store Interface\n12: //\n13: // The Store interface defines the contract for session storage backends:\n14: //\n15: //   - Ping(ctx): Verify connectivity to the storage backend\n16: //   - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID): Retrieve sandbox metadata by session ID\n17: //   - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox): Persist new sandbox metadata\n18: //   - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox): Update existing sandbox metadata\n19: //   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID): Remove sandbox and associated indices\n20: //   - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit): Query sandboxes expiring before a given time\n21: //   - ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit): Query sandboxes inactive before a given time\n22: //   - UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at): Update the last activity timestamp\n23: //   - Close(): Close the storage connection\n24: //\n25: // # Key Patterns\n26: //\n27: // Sessions are stored using the following key patterns:\n28: //   - session:{id} - JSON-encoded sandbox metadata\n29: //   - session:expiry - ZSET with score=ExpiresAt.Unix(), member=sessionID\n30: //   - session:last_activity - ZSET with score=LastActivityAt.Unix(), member=sessionID\n31: //\n32: // # Backends\n33: //\n34: // Redis Backend:\n35: //   - Uses github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 client library\n36: //   - Configured via REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED environment variables\n37: //   - Atomic operations use Redis pipelines\n38: //\n39: // Valkey Backend:\n40: //   - Uses github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go client library\n41: //   - Configured via VALKEY_ADDR, VALKEY_PASSWORD, VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED, etc.\n42: //   - Supports cluster mode with comma-separated addresses\n43: //   - Atomic operations use DoMulti\n44: //\n45: // # Singleton Pattern\n46: //\n47: // Access the storage instance via Storage():\n48: //\n49: //\tstore := Storage()\n50: //\terr := store.Ping(ctx)\n51: //\n52: // The singleton initializes exactly once using sync.Once. Provider selection is based on\n53: // the STORE_TYPE environment variable (case-insensitive):\n54: //   - \"redis\" (default): Use Redis backend\n55: //   - \"valkey\": Use Valkey backend\n56: //\n57: // # Configuration\n58: //\n59: // Environment variables:\n60: //   - STORE_TYPE: Storage provider type (default: \"redis\")\n61: //   - REDIS_ADDR: Redis server address (required for Redis)\n62: //   - REDIS_PASSWORD: Redis password (conditional)\n63: //   - REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED: Whether password is required (default: \"true\")\n64: //   - VALKEY_ADDR: Valkey server addresses, comma-separated (required for Valkey)\n65: //   - VALKEY_PASSWORD: Valkey password (conditional)\n66: //   - VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED: Whether password is required (default: \"true\")\n67: //   - VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE: Disable client-side caching (default: \"false\")\n68: //   - VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE: Force single-client mode (default: \"false\")\n69: //\n70: // # Error Handling\n71: //\n72: // ErrNotFound is returned when:\n73: //   - GetSandboxBySessionID is called with a non-existent session ID\n74: //   - UpdateSandbox is called for a session that doesn't exist\n75: //   - UpdateSessionLastActivity is called for a non-existent session\n76: //\n77: // List methods (ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes) tolerate orphaned ZSET members\n78: // by skipping missing keys rather than failing the entire batch.\n79: package store\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// Package store provides persistent storage for sandbox session metadata in the agentcube project.\n//\n// # Overview\n//\n// The session storage system enables:\n//   - Session persistence: Store and retrieve sandbox information keyed by session ID\n//   - Garbage collection support: Index sessions by expiry time and last activity for cleanup operations\n//   - Backend flexibility: Support both Redis and Valkey storage providers via configuration-based selection\n//   - Singleton access: Thread-safe initialization and global access pattern\n//\n// # Store Interface\n//\n// The Store interface defines the contract for session storage backends:\n//\n//   - Ping(ctx): Verify connectivity to the storage backend\n//   - GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID): Retrieve sandbox metadata by session ID\n//   - StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox): Persist new sandbox metadata\n//   - UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox): Update existing sandbox metadata\n//   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID): Remove sandbox and associated indices\n//   - ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit): Query sandboxes expiring before a given time","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/doc.go","time":{"start":1775857589764,"end":1775857589791}}}}
