{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857862903,"sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","part":{"id":"prt_d796083e8001rqP4CNPdrNsiuU","messageID":"msg_d79607aae001wXdC2h0uHFTp6Z","sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","type":"text","text":"I see the issue. The error message says \"valkey nil message\" which means the error is wrapped. Let me update the test to check for the correct error behavior. Looking at the spec and the implementation, the UpdateSandbox should return ErrNotFound when the key doesn't exist. Let me also fix the UpdateSessionLastActivity test:","time":{"start":1775857862902,"end":1775857862902}}}
