{"type":"text","timestamp":1775858044706,"sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","part":{"id":"prt_d79632e17001uoUFG6i5iliaeT","messageID":"msg_d796325260017Fzgrnq2y0RSsA","sessionID":"ses_286a45edbffeb2i4Bne1Azi1xR","type":"text","text":"The Valkey store implementation is complete. Let me provide a summary of what's implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've implemented the complete **AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现** (Valkey Store Implementation) for the agentcube project:\n\n### Files Created/Modified:\n\n1. **`pkg/store/store_valkey.go`** (already existed, 284 lines) - Complete Valkey implementation with:\n   - `valkeyStore` struct with client and key prefixes\n   - `makeValkeyOptions()` - Environment-based configuration\n   - `NewValkeyStore()` - Constructor\n   - All Store interface methods:\n     - `Ping()` - Health check\n     - `GetSandboxBySessionID()` - Retrieve sandbox by session ID\n     - `StoreSandbox()` - Create new sandbox (with SETNX)\n     - `UpdateSandbox()` - Update existing sandbox (with XX option)\n     - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` - Remove sandbox and indices\n     - `ListExpiredSandboxes()` - Query expired sessions by expiry ZSET\n     - `ListInactiveSandboxes()` - Query inactive sessions by activity ZSET\n     - `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` - Update last activity timestamp\n     - `Close()` - Close connection\n\n2. **`pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`** (already existed) - Unit tests for configuration\n\n3. **`pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`** (created, 520+ lines) - Comprehensive integration tests covering:\n   - All Store interface operations\n   - Error handling (nil sandbox, zero ExpiresAt, missing sessions)\n   - Edge cases (zero limit, negative limit, empty session ID, zero time)\n   - Idempotent delete operations\n   - Duplicate session prevention\n\n4. **`pkg/store/singleton.go`** (already existed) - Includes Valkey store type and initialization\n\n### Test Results:\nAll 38 tests pass including:\n- 22 Valkey-specific tests\n- 8 Redis tests (unchanged)\n- 8 general store tests\n\nThe implementation matches the spec requirements (R-1 through R-14) and follows the same interface and behavior as the Redis implementation.","time":{"start":1775858044704,"end":1775858044704}}}
